This paper proposes a deep learning model for emotion detection in textual conversations, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP). The paper also mentions the use of sentiment and semantic embeddings, which are techniques commonly used in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with emotions, which can be related to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of semi-automated techniques to gather training data, which can be related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
